{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"56a8992bd1ae6f1ef859ec2721d792bc3f3db2cdc3c409e5b18097ec03aaea28","slug":"public-oriented-data-science","location":"/professional_advice/public_oriented_data_science.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Public-Interest Data Science Jobs","content_includes_title":false,"github":"https://github.com/MIDS-at-Duke/dukemids","numbering":{"title":{"offset":1}},"source_url":"https://github.com/MIDS-at-Duke/dukemids/blob/main/professional_advice/public_oriented_data_science.md","edit_url":"https://github.com/MIDS-at-Duke/dukemids/edit/main/professional_advice/public_oriented_data_science.md","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"public_oriented_data_science.md","url":"/build/public_oriented_data-448100f233eefd185454464f19a2fd67.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So you’re a data scientist interested in using your skills to contributing to the public good. At the same time, you aren’t sure a job with the government (federal, state, or local) or a non-profit is right for you. This is not an uncommon position to find yourself in — many young data scientists want to give back, but are also nervous about the practicalities of things like student loans and visa sponsorship. As discussed below, however, there are many paths to doing good with your data science degree, and ","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"JyrYRNdmrF"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"many of them actually come with ","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"RvcCJKznvE"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"increased","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"F3ZQxP7WBL"}],"key":"QVE62AklVo"},{"type":"text","value":" job security and an easier path to securing a green card.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"OKXytjGyjc"}],"key":"G84NK5gVe5"}],"key":"KuBUHjB5kH"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Considerations for Jobs in the Public Interest","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"rBI45oCZ1D"}],"identifier":"considerations-for-jobs-in-the-public-interest","label":"Considerations for Jobs in the Public Interest","html_id":"considerations-for-jobs-in-the-public-interest","implicit":true,"key":"t3l7wlC9VH"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"While not all jobs that contribute to the public good offer the same salary as one might get working for a major tech company like Google or NVIDIA, you may be surprised by the benefits on offer for data scientists who take public interest jobs.","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"DLvIeWgZJS"}],"key":"feWda8rHYF"},{"type":"list","ordered":true,"start":1,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Many public-interest jobs offer quite competitive salaries.","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"Jtf994UV42"}],"key":"sBJVCUKVaR"},{"type":"text","value":" There are a surprising number of for-profit or not-for-profit companies that specialize in serving non-profit and government clients. These companies — like Civis Analytics, Mathematica, or Acumen — pay very reasonably. They don’t pay “meta just acquired my AI startup” salaries, but they are often more than adequate to cover your student loans.","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"nxUZbaKw9K"}],"key":"cKD56IzOoT"}],"key":"mZYps6xgO3"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Employees of certain non-profits can get H1B visas without going through the visa lottery system.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"kKqjgoUCPR"}],"key":"nI88J8JzTv"},{"type":"text","value":" Employees of non-profit or government research organizations (like universities, think tanks, or government research groups) are what are called ","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"vslfTKcG2i"},{"type":"link","url":"https://elevate.iit.edu/blog/2026/03/01/what-are-h-1b-cap-exempt-jobs/","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“H1B cap-exempt employers”","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"nvJB56XIAG"}],"urlSource":"https://elevate.iit.edu/blog/2026/03/01/what-are-h-1b-cap-exempt-jobs/","key":"m50JnJ0FP2"},{"type":"text","value":", can their employees can apply for H1Bs without worrying about getting one of those lucky draws.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"IkzEiObnOM"}],"key":"UTwIIsrg1Q"}],"key":"s689bKveez"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Just because the job title isn’t “data scientist” or “data engineer” doesn’t mean it isn’t a data science job.","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"CDHbAGftk0"}],"key":"YGmCGX3YPf"},{"type":"text","value":" Non-profits and government consultants often don’t use keywords the same way as big tech companies. For jobs in these sectors, “Data and Policy Analyst” or “Data Analyst” may be for precisely the same jobs as what a big tech company might call “Data Scientist” or “Data Engineering.” And a lot of medical research groups seem to list data science jobs under “IT” alongside jobs like EPIC (an EMR program) trainer. And remember, a job whose label or categorization may be off is a job that will attract fewer qualified applicants, so HR’s poor keyword management is your gain!","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"be6MGesrTS"}],"key":"roVvZvhEc2"}],"key":"ifDKvk5Dau"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Companies with government clients often offer substantially better job security than the for-profit private sector,","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"GIvit6gOqQ"}],"key":"NtIPQ9Fwc2"},{"type":"text","value":" especially companies who have contracts with the federal government.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"ytk6snsWQ8"}],"key":"Gc0a65rNKq"}],"key":"g6vCcTSxbt"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"lin